Czech Coalition Moots Raising Corporate Tax, Hospodarske Reports

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-03-04T06:48:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/czech-coalition-moots-raising-corporate-tax-hospodarske-reports.html
Czech government coalition parties
are considering raising the corporate tax rate to 20 percent
from 19 percent,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing Michal
Babak, a member of the Public Affairs party.  Public Affairs and its two ruling-coalition partners are
debating how to overhaul the tax system, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporters on this story:  Peter Laca  in  Prague  at 
 placa@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  